SIMPLE: festi-val
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Festi-val
<hw>Fes"ti-val</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A time of feasting or
celebration; an anniversary day of joy, civil or religious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The morning trumpets <qex>festival</qex> proclaimed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Feast; banquet; carousal. See
<er>Feast</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Festive</ent>⟦br⟧
